The paper deals with tradeoffs between quantum communication complexity and quantum query complexity, which are central topics in computational complexity theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves information theory concepts such as mutual information and entropy, which suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses lower bounds for searching databases, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper includes a generalization of the tradeoff for distributional query complexity, which is a topic in cs.LG (Machine Learning).
